AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - RUSSIA (14): (KALMYKIA, KRASNODAR), SUSPECTED,
REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
********************************************************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Fri 7 Oct 2011
Source: News portal rbc.ru [trans. summ. Corr.ATS, edited]
http://www.rbc.ru/rbcfreenews.shtml?/20111007185413.shtml


Another outbreak of African swine fever (ASF) has been registered in
Kalmykia. The Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary
Surveillance [Rosselkhoznadzor] has announced that they have
identified ASF virus in the carcass of a pig from an irrigation canal
4 km downstream from the settlement of Proletarskiy of Yashaltinskiy
rayon. The regional veterinary authority has undertaken to investigate
the matter and limit the spread of the infection.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-RUS@promedmail.org>

[A confirmation of this outbreak has not been found in
Rosselkhoznadzor's web-site and is hereby requested. For the location
of the Republic of Kalmykia, see http://healthmap.org/r/1kIR and
http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/media/images/40578000/gif/_40578127_moscow_kalmykia_map203.gif.
- Mod.AS]

******
[2]
Date: Mon 10 Oct 2011
Source: News agency news.mail.ru [trans. summ. Corr.ATS, edited]
http://news.mail.ru/incident/7029184/


According to the regional veterinary authority, a new focus of ASF has
been found in a private farm in the village Staroleushkovskoe in
Pavlovski rayon. The affected farm has 56 swine. It has been decided
to cull all animals in the 1st "risk zone" around the outbreak, which
includes an estimate of more than 2700 animals. As of the report date,
593 animals have been destroyed and burned.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-rus@promedmail.org>

[The above outbreak was notified by Russia to the OIE in follow-up
report No 67, submitted 12 Oct 2011; see, with interactive map, at
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=11130.

An International Seminar "Set of measures for prevention of African
Swine Fever Spread" is to be held at the All-Russian Exhibition
Centre, Moscow on 14 Oct 2011 at 12.30 p.m. in the framework of the
agro-industrial exhibition "Golden Autumn 2011." Russian and
international experts (EU, Spain and others) are due to participate. -
Mod.AS]
